=Description=

"One of the challenges of data protection, and especially the protection of minors, is to have rules which are dynamic and jurisdiction-sensitive and at the same time allow for role-based permissioning ranging from parents, peers, and law enforcement. When considered together, these can be quite complex. What the Rule of Law Engine demonstrates is that it is possible to express complex privacy policies, execute these privacy policies on a mobile platform using location data, coupled with verified credentials and information about the individual. This is work in progress, but we expect to be using this rule of law engine within our Open Mustard Seed Trust Framework project in the near future. "
(http://idcubed.org/digital-law/rule-of-law-engine/)

